```typescript
export interface SelectedLabel {
  category: string;
  subtype: string | null;
  confidence: number;
  score: number;          // REQUIRED - missing in all test objects
  isPrimary: boolean;
  labelOrder: number;     // REQUIRED - missing in all test objects
  selectionRationale: string;
}
```

So I need to add `score` and `labelOrder` properties to all the SelectedLabel objects in the test file. Since the test objects already have `confidence` set, I'll use that same value for `score`. For `labelOrder`, I'll use 1 for primary labels and sequential numbers for secondary labels.

Let me fix all the occurrences systematically.

